{"type":"message","id":"27b31202","parentId":"e9ac7369","timestamp":"2026-03-15T10:58:13.935Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u9fmaw7mwh5e_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\prose.md:88:��       ������ bindings/\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:106:- optional **agent binding** \r\n(`agentId`): run the job under a specific agent; if\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\cron-jobs.md:349:- Use `agentId: null` in the \r\npatch to clear an agent binding.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\automation\\gmail-pubsub.md:161:gcloud pubsub topics add-i\r\nam-policy-binding gog-gmail-watch \\\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\broadcast-groups.md:73:Add a top-level `broadcas\r\nt` section (next to `bindings`). Keys are WhatsApp peer ids:\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\broadcast-groups.md:164:   - Normal routing appl\r\nies (first matching binding)\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\broadcast-groups.md:290:  \"bindings\": [\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\broadcast-groups.md:305:**Precedence:** `broadca\r\nst` takes priority over `bindings`.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\broadcast-groups.md:325:**Cause:** Peer ID might\r\n be in `bindings` but not `broadcast`.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\broadcast-groups.md:327:**Fix:** Add to broadcas\r\nt config or remove from bindings.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\channel-routing.md:62:1. **Exact peer match** (`\r\nbindings` with `peer.kind` + `peer.id`).\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\channel-routing.md:71:When a binding includes mu\r\nltiple match fields (`peer`, `guildId`, `teamId`, `roles`), **all provided fields must match** for that binding to appl\r\ny.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\channel-routing.md:96:- `bindings`: map inbound \r\nchannels/accounts/peers to agents.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\channel-routing.md:105:  bindings: [\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:465:Use `bindings[].match.roles` to r\r\noute Discord guild members to different agents by role ID. Role-based bindings accept role IDs only and are evaluated a\r\nfter peer or parent-peer bindings and before guild-only bindings. If a binding also sets other match fields (for exampl\r\ne `peer` + `guildId` + `roles`), all configured fields must match.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:469:  bindings: [\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:648:    - `/unfocus` remove current t\r\nhread binding\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:649:    - `/agents` show active runs \r\nand binding state\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:650:    - `/session idle <duration|of\r\nf>` inspect/update inactivity auto-unfocus for focused bindings\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:651:    - `/session max-age <duration\r\n|off>` inspect/update hard max age for focused bindings\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:658:    threadBindings: {\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:666:      threadBindings: {\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:679:    - `session.threadBindings.*` \r\nsets global defaults.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:680:    - `channels.discord.threadBin\r\ndings.*` overrides Discord behavior.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:683:    - If thread bindings are disa\r\nbled for an account, `/focus` and related thread binding operations are unavailable.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:689:  <Accordion title=\"Persistent AC\r\nP channel bindings\">\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:690:    For stable \"always-on\" ACP wo\r\nrkspaces, configure top-level typed ACP bindings targeting Discord conversations.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:694:    - `bindings[]` with `type: \"a\r\ncp\"` and `match.channel: \"discord\"`\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:716:  bindings: [\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:746:    - Thread messages can inherit\r\n the parent channel ACP binding.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:748:    - Temporary thread bindings s\r\ntill work and can override target resolution while active.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:750:    See [ACP Agents](/tools/acp-a\r\ngents) for binding behavior details.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:1209:- features: `threadBindings`, to\r\np-level 