ll accounts) and is less specific than an explicit account binding.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:54:- If the same agent already has a matchi\r\nng channel binding without `accountId`, and you later bind with an explicit or resolved `accountId`, OpenClaw upgrades \r\nthat existing binding in place instead of adding a duplicate.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:59:# initial channel-only binding\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:62:# later upgrade to account-scoped bindin\r\ng\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:66:After the upgrade, routing for that bind\r\ning is scoped to `telegram:ops`. If you also want default-account routing, add it explicitly (for example `--bind teleg\r\nram:default`).\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:68:Remove bindings:\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:44:If you confirm bind now, the wizard as\r\nks which agent should own each configured channel account and writes account-scoped routing bindings.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:46:You can also manage the same routing r\r\nules later with `openclaw agents bindings`, `openclaw agents bind`, and `openclaw agents unbind` (see [agents](/cli/age\r\nnts)).\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:52:- Existing channel-only bindings (no `\r\naccountId`) continue to match the default account.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:53:- `channels add` does not auto-create \r\nor rewrite bindings in non-interactive mode.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:54:-