ing\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:39:openclaw agents bindings --json\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:42:Add bindings:\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:50:### Binding scope behavior\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:52:- A binding without `accountId` matches \r\nthe channel default account only.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:53:- `accountId: \"*\"` is the channel-wide f\r\nallback (all accounts) and is less specific than an explicit account binding.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:54:- If the same agent already has a matchi\r\nng channel binding without `accountId`, and you later bind with an explicit or resolved `accountId`, OpenClaw upgrades \r\nthat existing binding in place instead of adding a duplicate.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:59:# initial channel-only binding\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:62:# later upgrade to account-scoped bindin\r\ng\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:66:After the upgrade, routing for that bind\r\ning is scoped to `telegram:ops`. If you also want default-account routing, add it explicitly (for example `--bind teleg\r\nram:default`).\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agents.md:68:Remove bindings:\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:44:If you confirm bind now, the wizard as\r\nks which agent should own each configured channel account and writes account-scoped routing bindings.\r\nC:\\Users\\73911\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\channels.md:46:Yo